4: Decorator

Decorators let you add extra behavior to a function, without changing the function's code. A decorator

def login_required(func):
    def wrapper(user):
        if not user.get("logged_in"):
            print("Access Denied ❌")
            return
        return func(user)
    return wrapper


@login_required
def dashboard(user):
    print("Welcome to dashboard")


user1 = {"logged_in": True}
user2 = {"logged_in": False}

dashboard(user1)
dashboard(user2)

